<title>Med-Media - How to order</title>
<!!keys: >
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<hr>
<h1>How to Order</h1>

MED-MEDIA programmes are available to broadcasters and other users on conditions which vary from country to country.

<h3>Broadcasters - In Europe</h3>

If MED-MEDIA does not hold broadcast rights for  programmes in this folder which interest you, we will negotiate favourable rates for you.  If the broadcast rights are held by another distributor, your order will be referred to them. Special package rates are available and we will do our best to meet your budgets.


<h3>Broadcasters in the Southern and Eastern Mediterranean</h3>

MED-MEDIA films are available to you on a cost recovery basis, of £150 per Beta Master.

A package rate is available at £750 per 10 Films on Beta masters



<h3>Non-broadcaster users</h3>

All these films are available on VHS cassettes, for use in education and training.  This means that they can only be purchased by schools, colleges, universities, hospitals, businesses, non-profit associations, etc. No admittance fee may be charged  for seeing programmes supplied for 'non-theatric' education and training use. Films are available at £30 per VHS cassette,  or at £200 per 10 films.

<h3>Ordering</h3>

All orders, both broadcast and non-broadcast, should be sent to the Television Trust for the Environment  (TVE), for the attention of Terry Hackett MED-MEDIA Distribution Manager, Prince Albert Road, London

NW1 4RZ. Telephone: (+44 71) 586 5526 Fax: (+44 71) 586 4866. (Winfax +44 71 722 9697) 
<p>



<ol>Please make sure your order contains the following information:

<li>	Customer name

<li>	Invoice adress

<li>	Delivery adress including postcode,

and telephone number

<li>	Title of video(s)

<li>	Tape format required

<li>	Language version required 

<li>	VAT number (for all orders from 

European Union countries)
</ol>
<p>
An <a href="order.html" target="_new">Online Order Form</a> is also available.


<h3>Payment</h3>

All orders must be paid in advance.<p>


If you are ordering from overseas TVE will supply you with a pro forma invoice which gives details of how to pay by bank transfer.  Payments by sterling cheque or bank draft should be made payable to <b>'Television Trust for the Environment'.</b>
<p>

<hr> <p>
<a href="index.html">Medmedia Home Page</a>
</body>
