<html>
<head>
<title>Med-Media Film Reviews</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF">
<center>
<p>
<br><h1>Building Bridges: </h1><h2>Co-productions and MED-MEDIA Film Reviews</h2><br clear=left></center>

<hr><br>
<p><br><h3>HANAN ASHRAWI - A WOMAN OF HER TIME</h3>
<a href="ashrawi.html">Click here</a> for a special feature - including a video clip to download -  on this 50 minute documentary about former PLO spokeswoman Hanan Ashrawi, made by Palestinian Director Mai Masri.<br clear=right>
<p>
<hr><p>



<h3>WOMEN OF GAZA</h3>
<b>COUNTRY:</b> Palestine, UK<br>
<b>YEAR:</b> 1995<br>
<b>LENGTH:</b> 60'<br>
<b>LANGUAGE:</b> English<br>
<b>PRODUCER/ DIRECTOR:</b> Antonia Caccia<p>
<a href="gaza.mov">Click here for a preview (1.6Mb)</a><p><br clear=left>
We were warned that most women would be afraid to speak about their lives in front of the camera, and that they would need permission from either their father, brothers, husbands or sons. Indeed we did have to put a lot of effort into obtaining permits and permissions. However once the women were alone in front of the camera, we were struck by how openly and intimately they were prepared to speak. 

<p>
<hr>

<p>
<h3> MAN ON THE MOVE</h3>



<b>COUNTRY:</b> Denmark, Jordan<br>

<b>YEAR: </b>1994 <br>           <b>LENGTH: 3 x 20'</b><br>

<b>LANGUAGE: </b>Danish, English<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO: </b>Arena Films<br>

<b>PRODUCER/DIRECTOR:</b> Jim Groser<p>
<a href="medman.mov">Click here for a preview (1.1Mb)</a><p>
<br clear=right>


Travelling on a Danish train, a young boy sits opposite a mysterious stranger who turns out to be 100,000 years old. The boy is entrusted with a talisman - a timeless objects which holds the secret of eternal life - and, in a series of flashbacks, the 100,000 year-old man tells him the story of his long life, from his birth in the Stone Age period to the present day. It is the story of the human migrations, and the irresistible economic and climatic forces that fuelled those migrations over the centuries. By weaving the educational message into an innovative storylineJim Groser has created a powerful allegory about the inevitability of migration throughout history.
<br clear=left>


<p>
<hr><p>



<p><br>
<h3>ON THE BORDER</h3>


<b>COUNTRY: </b>Denmark, Israel, Germany<br>

<b>YEAR:</b> 1994 <br>           <b>LENGTH: </b>26'<br>

<b>LANGUAGE: </b>English<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO:</b> Novavision, Afikim Productions<br>

<b>DIRECTOR: </b>Gert Ellegaard, Danish<p>


<br clear=left>

The border between Denmark and Germany, agreed after a referendum in 1920, has been undisputed for over 70 years. The border between the Occupied Territories and Israel is one

of the bloodiest, the most debated and the most vulnerable in the world. A study of the psychological need men and nations have to create boundaries, this co-production between Novavision and Afikim Films looks at  the lives of people whose existence is dominated by the presence of borders.<p><br clear=right>


<p>


<hr>


<p>






<h3>SONG OF THE SEA</h3>
<b>COUNTRY: </b> Greece<br>

<b>YEAR: </b>1994 <br>           <b>LENGTH:</b> 60'<br>

<b>LANGUAGE: </b>English<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO: </b>International Video Association<br>

<b>PRODUCER/DIRECTOR: </b>Christopher Klint<p>
<a href="songofsea.mov">Click here for a preview (1.9Mb)</a><p>



Director Christopher Klint's lyrical documentary is the record of an odyssey around the Mediterranean sea - by felucca, caique and trireme - in search of the traditional music, song and dance of the region. His wanderings take him from the smouldering volcanic Eolian islands off the northern coast of Sicily, where the inhabitants still sing of the horrors perpetrated by the corsair Barbarossa, to his mausoleum on the shores of the Bosphorus in Istanbul.<p>




<hr><p>


<h3>VIEWS OF THE HOLY LAND</h3>



<b>COUNTRY:</b> UK, Jordan<br>

<b>YEAR: </b>1994 <br>           <b>LENGTH: </b>60'<br> 

<b>LANGUAGE:</b> English<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO:</b> Lowndes Associates<br>

<b>PRODUCER/DIRECTOR: </b>Douglas Lowndes, Scotland<p>

<a href="holyland.mov">Click here for a preview (2.7Mb)</a><p>
<br clear=left><p>


Scottish artist David Roberts' drawings of the Arab world were first published as a book of lithographs in 1842. In Victorian England - in the fervour of British empire - the book was an overnight success, giving its travel hungry, Bible-reared readers their first impression of the Holy Lands of Egypt, Palestine, Lebanon and Syria. Director Douglas Lowndes has a long history of productions exploring cultural themes, and his latest film has recreated the seminal journey Roberts took through the Holy Land.


<p><hr><p>


<h3>LES FANTOMES DU MONDE</h3>



<b>COUNTRY:</b> France, Tunisia, Greece<br>

<b>YEAR:</b>  1994 <br>          <b>LENGTH:</b>  3 x  25'<br>

<b>LANGUAGE:</b> French<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO: </b>Centre Méditerranéen de la Communication Audiovisuelle (CMCA)<br>

<b>PRODUCER/DIRECTOR:</b>Henri Dumolie, Francois Werner, France<p>
<a href="lesfantomes.mov">Click here for a preview (2.1Mb)</a><p>


<br clear=left>

Beneath the deceptive calm of the Mediterranean Sea lies a wealth of history, stored in the wrecks of all the ships that have fallen victim to the unpredictable Mediterranean weather and sunk without trace. The second trilogy of films in the co-production series initiated by CMCA explores three new shipwrecks off the coast of Tunisia, France and Crete. The first two date from the second half of the 17th century, the third from the dawn of Christianity

<p>
<hr><p>






<h3>LIFE IN ALLAH'S GARDEN</h3>



<b>COUNTRY:</b> Algeria, Germany<br>

<b>YEAR:</b> 1994 <br>           <b>LENGTH: </b>30'<br>

<b>LANGUAGE:</b>English<br>

<b>PRODUCTION CO:</b><br>Tele-International-Dresden-GmbH<br>

<b>PRODUCER/DIRECTOR:</b> Adnan Ramahi<p>
<a href="tassili.mov">Click here for a preview (2.4Mb)</a><p>



The paintings in the caves of Tassili National Park - a world heritage site 2,000 km south of Algiers in the Hoggar Desert - represent one of the greatest records of human development found anywhere in the world. Director Adnan Ramahi's documentary - filmed under extremely difficult circumstances in March 1994 - looks at their history, and current attempts to preserve them.

<br clear=right><br clear=left>
<br>
