<html>
<head>
<title>Hanan Ashrawi - A Woman of her Time</title>
</head>
<body bgcolor="#000000" text="#A8A8A8">

<center></center>


<p>
<center>



</center><p>


<p>
<center><h3>A 50 minute documentary on the former PLO spokeswoman <b>Hanan Ashrawi</b> made by Palestinian Director <b>Mai Masri</b> as part of <br>TVE's <i>Developing Stories</i></h3><p>

<a href="ashrawi.mov"><h3>Click here for a preview (movie file, 1.5 Mb)</h3></a></center><br clear=left>


<p>


In the stormy aftermath of 1993's peace accord between Israel and the PLO, former Palestinian spokeswoman Hanan Ashrawi has emerged as a formidable negotiator and a persuasive voice on the international stage. But beyond the polished rhetoric and the public poise, what drives the 47-year-old mother of two who twice turned down the Ministry of Information portfolio out of fears she would end up running a Palestinian censorship department? Ashrawi's high profile and personal integrity have made her enemies as well as friends. In this intimate document by fellow Palestinian Mai Masri, she recalls her Christian upbringing, her formative teenage years at the American University in Beirut, and her first meeting with Yasser Arafat. She also gives an insider's account of the intricate negotiations with Israel, describes the secret Oslo peace channel she created from her own home, and confronts the challenges ahead for the PLO in the struggle to build a viable homeland state.<p>




<p>
<p>


 
