</TR></TABLE><hr></center>
<FONT COLOR="#3333FF"><H2 align=center>FALKLANDS CONSERVATION</H2></FONT>
<FONT COLOR="#3333FF"><H3 align=center>Protecting the Unique Wildlife of the Falkland Islands and the South Atlantic</H3></FONT>
<dl><dt><dd><B>Welcome to Falklands Conservation, the UK charity founded by the late Sir Peter Scott and fellow conservationists in 1979 to monitor and protect the exceptional wildlife heritage of the Falkland Islands. The Islands are one of the last great wilderness sites on Earth and form a unique bridge between the Antarctic and Subantarctic and the South American continent.</B><P>
</dl>

<TABLE BORDER=0 align=left>
<TR>
<TD></TD>
<TR><TH><small>Rockhopper Penguin logo<br>by Sir Peter Scott</small></TH>
</TD>
</TR>
</TABLE>
The Falklands and their marine surroundings are rich in wildlife:<BR>
<UL><LI> home to vast colonies of penguins and albatrosses
<LI> breeding grounds for sea lions, elephant seals and fur seals
<LI> 15 species of whales and dolphins
<LI> more than 150 native flowering plant species grow in the Islands, 12 of which are endemic
<LI> many unique insects including the rare and beautiful Queen of the Falklands Fritillary butterfly
<LI> at least 200 species of birds have been recorded, of which more than 60 breed, including two endemic species (the Falkland Flightless Steamer Duck and Cobb's Wren) and 12 endemic races, plus the rare and local Johnny Rook (Striated Caracara) and Ruddy-headed  Goose<P>
</UL>
<FONT COLOR="#3333FF"><B>Falklands Conservation is the only specialist organisation of its type operating in the area.  We need your help to look after the flora and fauna of this region of major world conservation significance. </B></FONT><P>

<B>Contents</B><BR>
<UL><LI><b><a href="map.html">Where are the Falklands?</a></b>
<LI><b><A HREF = "urgent.html">Urgent need</A></b>  for protection and what we're doing about it
<LI>How to make a <b><A HREF = "donor.html">donation</A></b> to our work
<LI>How to become a <b><A HREF = "member.html">Member</A></b>
<LI><b><a href=mailto:chris@crispage.demon.co.uk>Contact us</a></b>
</UL><P>
