November 1995<br>
Issue 6/95</b><br><br>

<li><b><a href="../index_oc/recent.html#britain">Liberty in Britain</a></b><br>
The days when the death penalty was in retreat around the world are no more.  In the USA in particular, states expedite executions and elected officials vow to 'get tough on crime'.  In Britain, promises of more open government have made little impression on the culture of secrecy that dominates hte life of the state and denies its citizens the rights to know.<br>
<b>Read this issue free by clicking on the title<br>
April 1995<br>
Issue 2 1995</b><p>

