<b><li>A Guide to Rights</b><br>
Written by young people for young people, this booklet summarises
and clarifies the United Nations Convention on the Rights of the
Child.  The guide describes the rights enshrined in the articles
of the convention through personal accounts and drawings.  The
articles are grouped together to make it easier to understand and
relate them to real life situations that affect young people. 
This resource will be invaluable to young people, practitioners
working on children's rights and those who want to promote the UN
Convention in their work.<br>
<b>£2.00<br>
