<CENTER><A NAME="Values and Visions"><H3>VALUES AND VISIONS</H3></A></CENTER> 

A development education project to encourage spiritual development and global awareness</H4> </CENTER> <HR>
<BODY>
<H3><B>Summary:</B></H3>
The Values and Visions project has been operating for the past 4 years to become an effective means for bringing spiritual development and global awareness to primary schools. This has taken the form of a framework, methodology and teaching activities bought to schools through an inservice training programme and in some cases through in depth work with all school staff. This experience has been encapsulated in the teachers' manual.<P> 

This project addresses a fundamental concern to develop community in schools. It builds on much that has been done in the past but is essentially innovatory. It seeks to develop community in school through an acknowledgement of the importance of shared vaues and visions; through a focus on issues of justice, peace and the environment; through recognising the spiritual development that underpins this work.<P> 


<B>The project and <A HREF="values_handbook.html">handbook</A> offer:</B><UL> <li>practical classroom activities and a methodology to bring spiritual development and global awareness into the school<BR> <li>strategies to enhance the sense of community especially where cultural and social differences are thought to be divisive<BR> <li>long term in-depth work on a whole school basis working with teachers, non teaching staff, governors and parents<BR> <li>experienced trainers some of whom are Southern ("Third World") partners and members of various faith groups</UL><P> <A HREF="values_handbookmap.html">Would you like to explore the handbook?</A><P> 


<B>The most apparent benefits were:</B><UL> <li>An increased level of staff awareness and professional confidence<BR> <li>The use of the ideas and activities were helpful on a practical level, eg in one school 'Here I Am' is being supported by the Guidelines throughout the school<BR> <li>An increased awareness around environmental studies both in terms of the level of knowledge, and in terms of care and commitment<BR> <li>Supporting work on children's behaviour: in one school Values and Visions is helping to take things forward in the areas of racism and bullying; in the other it is used to help co-operation.</ul> 

For more information contact <A HREF="dep.html">Manchester Development Education Project</A>, c/o MMU, 801 Wilmslow Road, Didsbury, Manchester M20 2QR, UK. Tel: (44) 161-445-2495. Fax: (44) 161-445-2360.<BR> 
<a href=mailto:depman@gn.apc.org>Email: depman@gn.apc.org</a> <P>

Go back to <A HREF="index.html">"What is Development Education?"</A> </BODY><HR NOSHADE>
