<b><li>Building With Bamboo<br>
A handbook (second edition) </b><br>
<i>Jules J.A. Janssen</i><br>
 This revised handbook brings together the practical experience of engineers working in the field, and research programmes testing the properties of bamboo. The book shows how bamboo has been used in different designs in developing countries and describes the varying properties and uses of different types of bamboo. The author shows how bamboo can be harvested, seasoned and jointed to form walls, doors and windows, roofs, floors, ceilings, roof trusses and bridges, and how to weave bamboo. <p>

The new edition updates and corrects the text of the first edition; and includes a detailed case study of the extensive experience of Costa Rica in bamboo construction. <p> 

Praise for the first edition:<br>
<i>'Written in clear, simple English . . . illustrations are well labelled and captioned ... [this book] should serve the needs of many people who are using bamboo for construction purposes in the developing countries.'	-- A.N. Rao </i> BambooNewsletter</i><br>
 <b>September 1994<br>
80pp<br>
Paperback<br>
246 x 174mm<br>
ISBN 1 85339 203 0</b><br><br><br>

<B><li>Developing Building for Safety Programmes<br>
Guidelines for organizing safe building programmes in disaster-prone areas</b><BR>
<I>Yasemin Aysan, Andrew Clayton, Alistair Cory, Ian Davis<BR>
</I>
The concluding book in the 'Building for Safety' series, <I>Developing
Building for Safety Programmes</I> offers practical guidelines on planning and implementing community- based building improvement programmes for small dwellings in disaster-prone areas. It includes sections on programme finance management and evaluation; safety principles for earthquake flood and high wind resistant construction; training and communication; social, cultural and developmental factors.<p>

In highlighting key elements of successful programme
design the books draws lessons from a large number of case studies worldwide which are included as an appendix.Asia and the Pacific is an extremely diverse region, containing both very small and very large nation states - as well as extremes of rich and poor. This volume describes the important and delicate role of the Asian Development Bank in this region during a dramatic period of economic transformation.<BR>
<B>£7.95, US $15.50<br>
September 1995<br>
Paperback<br>
120pp<br>
246 x 174mm<br>
ISBN 1 85339 184 0
<BR></b>
<BR><br>


