<b><li>Impact of urbanisation on groundwater quality, R5545</b><br>
<i>Adrian Lawrence<br>
WC/94/56</i><br>
Project work in Bolivia, Mexico and Thailand, to investigate the impact of rapid urbanisation on different types of shallow aquifer in varied climatic environments, is reported. Increased recharge and declining groundwater levels result from poorly controlled urban growth, reflecting leakage of wastewaters and increased abstraction of groundwater. Elevated nitrate and chloride concentrations and contamination of groundwaters by pathogens are also described. A follow-up study investigating impacts on deep aquifers is in progress.<p>

<b><li>Impact of urbanisation on groundwater in Merida, Mexico: final report<br>
WC/94/38</b>
(Project 91/13, R5545)<br>
British Geological Survey, Autonomous University of Yucatan and National Water Commission of Mexico <p>

<b><li>Networks for Urban Action</b><br>
Effective communication is one of the key tools for fostering a sense of common purpose and developing links which are of value to all stakeholders.  The Urban Management Programme for Asia and the Pacific (UMPAP) has released a guidebook that aims to facilitate networking amongst organisations working on urban issues.  Networks for Urban Action lists major global and regional initiatives that have an impact on the Asia/Pacific region.  <p>


The document provides a guide to which organisations are active, in what field and where, giving brief descriptions of the programme(s) and contact information. It is hoped that in time, this information will be made available electronically. <br>
