<b><li>World Urbanisation Prospect: the 1994 Revision</b><br>

Estimates and projections are recognised tools for developing plans and stratagies in both urban and rural development circles.  The Department of Economic and Social Information and Policy Analysis of the United Nations has published the results of its revisions to projections on urban and rural populations and urban agglomerations for major areas, regions and countries of the world.  The publication analyses growth patterns or urban settlements and provides comparative figures on size and distribution, in addition to country-specific information sources together with definitions of urban populations used in each nation.  Targetted for use by city managers and urban planners.<br>
