<b><li>Urban Poverty in Asia: A Survey of Critical Issues</b><br>

This ADB publication provides an analysis of the problems of urban poverty as experienced in Asia.  The publication discusses issues concerning urbanisation and urban poverty, including topics such as patterns of urban growth, characteristics of the urban poor, access to housing, the physical and social infrastructure of the urban environment and aspects of the labour market.  Additional information is drawn from case studies in Bangladesh, India, Indonesia, Republic of Korea, Philippines, Sri Lanka and Thailand.<br>
