<b><li>HIV, AIDS & Sex: Information for young people</b><br>
<i>"I think many girls are too embarrassed to ask a boy to use condoms"<br></i>Mainly for those aged 14-18, the booklet examines HIV, AIDS and sex from a young person's perspective as well as providing practical information and advice.<p><br>

<b><li>Condoms, Pills & Other Useful Things</b><br>
<i>"What does 'going on the pill' mean?"</i><br>
Written with the help of young people for young people, this booklet aims to provide young people with the contraceptive information they need before having their first sexual relationship. Mainly for those age 13-17.<p><br>



<b><li>Young Gay Men Talking</b><br>
<i>"Once you realise that I'm me first it gets a lot easier. Not gay first, me second. it's the other way around"</i><br>
Providing basic information about HIV, this booklet can help young men who feel isolated and unhappy because of society's attitudes towards homosexuality. Mainly for those aged 14-19.<p><br>

<b><li>Talking To Teenagers About AIDS: A Guide For Parents</b><br>
<i>"If I asked them about sex they'd probably think 'little hussy'"</i><br>
