<a name="voluntary"><hr><br>

[Voluntary Service Overseas]<br clear=left><br><br>

<li><b>Care and Safe use of Hospital Equipment </b><br>
<b><i>Care and Safe use of Hospital Equipment </b></i>is a practical, user-friendly guide for hospital managers and people who work with hospital equipment on a day-to-day basis in the developing world.<p>
Good maintenance procedures for equipment and effective user training, fault-reporting and follow-up systems are a vital part of health care delivery. Yet the reality in low-resourced district hospitals and health centres is that funds and fully-trained maintenance staff are scarce. Information on medical equipment, if available at all, is pitched at a technical level that is far too specialised for managers and the day-to-day users.<p>
This book gives simple instructions to users on how to handle equipment correctly and safely in day-to-day use<br>
<li>contains basic technical information which can be used to train first-line maintenance staff<br>
<li>contains easy-to-follow checklists for users which can be posted near equipment to ensure its correct use<p>

